  "prompt": "How do I add question details digitally on Quora?",
  "response": "To add details to a question you've posted on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log In**: Make sure you are logged into your Quora account.\n\n2. **Find Your Question**: Locate the question you want to add details to by going to your profile and clicking on \"Questions\" or by using the search bar if you know the keywords.\n\n3. **Edit Option**: Once you've found your question, click on the question to open the detailed view. Look for the \"Edit\" option, which is usually located below the question.\n\n4. **Add Details**: Click on the \"Edit\" button. You'll see a text box or editor where you can add more information to your question. Here, you can include additional context, clarify your question, or specify what type of answers you're seeking.\n\n5. **Save Changes**: After you've added the necessary details, make sure to save your changes. This is often done by clicking a \"Save\" or \"Submit\" button.\n\nKeep in mind that Quora may have guidelines and community standards that discourage overly detailed or unclear questions, so ensure your additions enhance clarity and engagement. If you encounter any issues, it's helpful to check Quora's help section or community guidelines for more detailed instructions or to verify if there have been any updates to their interface.",
